JOB PURPOSE
The Assistant Manager assists the Manager and/or Director in daily deliverables to provide excellent service to clients. They provide financial information to management by researching and analysing accounting data; preparing reports, submitting the reports to the client and are able to coach junior staff in the department.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
• Handle full set of accounts and bank operations for clients. Assists to manage daily work with high complexity, including closing full set of books, SFC compliance documents, capital account, annual financial statements, profits tax returns with tax computations, trade and shipping services, and other tailor made management reports/ financial analysis;
• Maintains relationship with clients and internal/external stakeholders, including banks, auditors, IRD and other government departments on client company’s affairs, accounts, bank accounts, tax filing, etc.;
• Query management with internal and external- 3rd party stakeholders;
• Assist Manager in preparing proposal for clients;
• Supervises Senior Accountants, Accountants and Junior Accountants, and reviews draft deliverables;
• Assists Manager/Director to oversee daily operations of the Accounting department and to implement internal control procedures;
• Assists Manager/Director to train & coach junior staff;
• Assists Manager/Director to follow up on Debtors list (client invoices);
• Prepares and checks various reports as requested by clients;
• Prepares and supervises accountant audits.

JOB PURPOSE
Manages all matters of the Accounting & Tax Service department and ensures excellent quality of services performed to client companies, revenue grows according to targets, financial targets are met, and strong client relationships are maintained.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
• Set goals, objectives and strategies for the department and its business development;
• Review Key Performance Indexes for the Department and set action points for teams to follow up;
• Work with management team to ensure efficient and effective cooperation across different divisions;
• Supervise and coach Managers;
• Lead projects which require highly skilled resources, e.g. IFRS reporting/conversion, due diligence work based on agreed procedures, etc.;
• Maintain relationship with clients’ management (i.e. decision maker);
• Review deliverables to key clients;
• Develop new business opportunities in line with company objectives;
• Analyze market opportunities and develop market share statistics for business development;
• Identify opportunities for cross-selling of TMF services;
• Prepare proposals for new/existing clients;
• Monitor and control the billing, debt recovery and credit control actions in the Department;
• Provide authorized signatory for payment instruction, and ad hoc assistance for Finance Division;
• Work with HR on recruitment activities, performance review and employee relations matters;
• Attend conference and seminars for networking and development purposes;
• Perform other duties as assigned.

